##Ministry of Science and Technology Urgent Rapid Kit, 15 minutes to detect new coronavirus reliable?

A reagent that claims to be capable of rapid detection in 30 or even 15 minutes

Mostly at the expense of performance in exchange for speed

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 3,2020, a production staff of a biotechnology company in Jiangsu Province carried out the packaging of reagent finished products. China News Service, photo by Tang Dehong

Since the outbreak of the new crown disease, a large number of suspected patients in Wuhan could not be confirmed due to the limitation of the number of test kits and laboratories. Recently, Wuhan to all suspected patients with nucleic acid testing "zero" , detection capacity from the initial daily 200, increased to 8,000 daily. At the moment of the epidemic, a large number of suspected patients, asymptomatic infected people waiting for diagnosis, making the related testing products urgent needs.

On February 8, the Ministry of Science and Technology issued the notice of the Covid-192019-ncov on-site Rapid Detection Product Development Emergency Project Declaration Guidelines (hereinafter referred to as the guidelines) , which aims to break through the restrictions of existing detection technologies on personnel, detection sites and other conditions, to improve the efficiency and convenience of rapid detection is beneficial to the rapid diagnosis of suspected patients and the on-site screening of people in close contact.

The Ministry of Science and technology to collect emergency rapid inspection products, product development required within one to two weeks, at the latest a month and a half to obtain a clinical certificate, and listed the relevant assessment indicators.

A throat swab sample, placed in a small POS machine-sized nucleic acid detector, press the start button, half an hour after the test results. Rapid on-site inspection (POCT) , also known as "bedside inspection" , relies on portable instruments and reagents, customs quarantine inspectors, grass-roots epidemic prevention and control personnel and some community workers, rapid screening of suspected cases can be performed at the sampling site.

Unlike the complex process of real-time PCR (polymerase chain reaction) detection, POCT can be done outside of the lab and without the care of a professional in a level-iii suit, as long as the instructions are followed, this can also be done by an ordinary examiner or nurse who has had a brief training. The whole detection process can save at least 3 ~ 4 hours. Successful rapid screening will lay an important foundation for graded diagnosis and treatment throughout the country.

The Ministry of Science and technology to collect the COVID-19 field rapid detection products are three, respectively, nucleic acid field rapid detection equipment and reagents, Antigen rapid detection reagents and antibody rapid detection reagents.

A researcher from the state key laboratory of nucleic acid detection told China news weekly that the principle of the rapid detection of nucleic acid on site is the same as that of real time PCR, that is, gene amplification, a piece of RNA from the new coronavirus was reverse-transcribed into double-stranded DNA, which was amplified by DNA polymerase, and the gene fragment carrying the virus was amplified and then captured by a fluorescent probe, when the amplified virus concentration reaches a critical level, a fluorescent signal is generated, indicating that a new coronavirus has been detected in the sample.

The researchers point out that while integrated field-based rapid detection is portable and easy to perform compared to traditional PCR tests in the laboratory, its sensitivity may be affected if too much emphasis is placed on its "fast" nature. For example, in the guidelines for the rapid detection of nucleic acids in the assessment of indicators, stipulated that compared with traditional real-time PCR reagents, the detection rate (sensitivity) to no less than 95% . "This amounts to an artificial reduction in the sensitivity required for a rapid detection of nucleic acids that, in theory, should be comparable to real-time fluorescent PCR, " the researchers said.

In addition, the number of samples that can be detected by rapid nucleic acid detection in situ is very limited, which may be as few as 7 ~ 8 and as many as 10 or more. But in the laboratory uses the PCR instrument, generally may examine 96 samples each time, many may achieve 384.

Unlike nucleic acid field rapid detection, antigen rapid detection reagents and antibody rapid detection reagents are immune detection, through the collection of patients'serum, using the principle of combining virus antigen and antibody. Antibody testing is the use of antibodies to detect the presence of viral antigens in a patient's body. Antigen testing is the use of viral antigens to detect whether a patient's body has activated a specific antibody.

A CDC expert specializing in nucleic acid testing told China Newsweek that the immune test is faster than the nucleic acid test. The former usually takes only 15 to 30 minutes to produce results, but the sensitivity is not as good as the nucleic acid test. For example, the Guide's criteria state that rapid antigen detection reagents are required to detect more than 80% of nucleic acids. The equivalent of nucleic acid testing can detect 100 positive samples, antigen testing requires detection of only 80. "In fact, this goal is not easy to achieve, " the expert lamented.

At a technical level, nucleic acids can be amplified by more than a million times the size of a virus's genome, far outpacing the effects of immune amplification, the researchers said. This means that although immunoassays are fast, the detection rate for samples with low concentrations of the virus is low, resulting in missed detection.

In addition, compared with real-time PCR, the specificity of Antigen detection is poor, resulting in false positives. Previously, a medical device company in Zhejiang used "colloidal gold method" , developed a rapid screening of coronavirus test paper, can be 10 minutes results. The developers of the product pointed out that this test paper is aimed at the broad-spectrum primary screening of coronavirus, not just for the new coronavirus.

"Any detection of a gene fragment is the most direct, whereas the detection of immunity is indirect, " the experts said.

Many experts told China News weekly, whether it is a rapid test on site or a real-time PCR test in the laboratory, under the existing technical conditions, the shortening of the time generally have to some extent at the expense of sensitivity. In other words, it's more likely to be a false negative.

Recently, Shandong, Shanghai, Tianjin and other provinces and cities, a number of medical devices enterprises have launched in half an hour to detect the COVID-19 test kits. It is understood that the kit has entered the State Food and Drug Administration's emergency approval channel.

At present, the real-time fluorescent PCR detection takes 1-1.5 hours at the earliest, the researcher from the state key laboratory specializing in nucleic acid detection told China news weekly. Because, the fastest time to extract nucleic acid is 30 ~ 40 minutes, to expand at least 40 ~ 60 minutes.

Another technical expert from a kit manufacturer told China Newsweek that reagents that can be tested quickly in 30 minutes, or even 15 minutes, mostly sacrifice some of their performance for speed.

The disease control experts pointed out that molecular genetic diagnosis technology, specificity and sensitivity will always need to be balanced. Specificity is strong, sensitivity is relatively poor; sensitivity is good, specificity will be weakened. The choice of different target sites, primers and probes, and even the design of reaction system are to better balance these two characteristics.

In his view, from a technical point of view, in the sensitivity and specificity of the balance, compared to some of the rapid detection methods, the balance is still the best real-time PCR detection kit. From the past major epidemic point of view, whether it is Zaire Ebolavirus, swine flu or Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) , fluorescent quantitative PCR is still the country's first test.

At present, only nucleic acid reagents are used for the diagnosis of COVID-19 infections, and the development time of antibody detection reagents is longer than the cycle of nucleic acid detection reagents, said Takatomi, director of the CDC. At present, there have been more than antibody detection research institutions near the stage of clinical trials. But he stressed the need to speed up the verification of antibody detection kits in the early detection of Immunoglobulin m antibodies.

Peking University First Hospital, Director of the division of aspiration and critical care medicine at the University of California, San Francisco, also said that if there is a gap between the clinical results of rapid testing and what is expected, it is necessary to analyze the circumstances under which rapid testing is more appropriate, when do we need to do real-time PCR for validation. This will have a very good effect is, can greatly reduce the pressure sent to the laboratory, the laboratory pressure will be greatly reduced.

"In the future, the combination of several types of agents will definitely further increase the detection rate of COVID-19 pneumonia, " Takatomi said.
